{
  "texts": [
    "By the construction, ρ = refine [k] (ρ) a.e. outside R 0.",
    "It follows therefore that for any fixed k ∈ N, refine [k] (ρ) → ρ weak * as K → ∞.",
    "Since V is weak * open, the required K 0 exists by the definition of limit.",
    "Lemma 5.20.",
    "Suppose k 0 ≥ 0 and ρ ∈ L ∞ ([0, 1] d)."
  ]
}